  "extraction_instructions": "Extract structured data from service agreement documents. Follow these rules:\n1. Use null for any field not mentioned or not derivable from the document. Do not guess or infer.\n2. For scope_of_services, use a concise but faithful description of what the document says.\n3. Normalize all dates to YYYY-MM-DD ISO format. If only a relative timeframe is given, use due_within_days instead.\n4. Normalize amounts as numbers (no currency symbols, no commas). For ranges, extract the upper bound.\n5. auto_renew defaults to false if not mentioned. consequential_damages_excluded is true only if explicitly excluded.\n6. Always map the party providing services to service_provider and the party receiving services to client, regardless of labels used.\n7. For multi-party agreements, map primary service provider to service_provider, primary client to client, use secondary_client for additional parties.\n8. When compensation includes non-cash contributions, note them in payment_terms_note.\n9. For contingent fees, extract the stated amount and note the contingency in payment_terms_note.\n10. Use the key 'deliverables_or_milestones' consistently — never 'milestones' or 'deliverables'.",
